# API specification (organization template)

> Set the **authoritative spec path** and **codegen command** in **`AGENTS.md`** for this repository.

## Source of truth

- The OpenAPI (or equivalent) document defines HTTP contracts.
- **Update the spec first** when adding or changing endpoints or schemas.

## Codegen

- After spec changes, run the project’s documented codegen (e.g. Zod schemas, React Query hooks, types).
- **Never hand-edit** generated output directories; fix the spec or generator config instead.

## Compatibility

- Prefer backward-compatible changes (optional fields, additive endpoints).
- If a breaking change is required, version the API or coordinate a migration (document in AGENTS.md / CHANGELOG).

## Response shape

- Keep a **consistent envelope** across endpoints if the project defines one (e.g. `success`, `data`, `error`, optional `warnings` / `messages`).
